{
  "text": "The above proof is R. J. Blattner's \"cleaner\" version of our original argument, we thank him for pointing it out to us. The assumption about the cocommutativity of H cannot be removed, for, as shown in [CITATION_1] , there exist graded rings (i.e. H = (fcG)*, G & non-abelian group) whose center is not graded.",
